rd.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bard speed</span><hr size=1> Im a 43 skald, so I have the top Skald speed spell.<br>
<br>
Last week I was out in emain (as you do) and I was running along solo.  I ran through mmg, and ran straight through a pack of hibs. (I can only imagine what they thought of a solo skald sprinting through!).  Anyway, I hit sprint because I had no chance against a full group.   I kept pressing f-11 so I could tell how close they were behind, and each time they were getting closer and closer.  Before my endurance had even reached 1/2 they had attacked me (melee) - how the hell did they even catch me?<br>
<br>
So I went back, and the same group found me around the Albion pk.  This time I had a good 5-10 second head start, but they still caught me within 20 seconds tops.<br>
<br>
My question is, is the bard speed song that fast?  How could they have caught me when I'm using the 43 bs speed song, combined with sprint?<br>
<br>
I think it sucks if I'm running at the top Midgard speed, yet they can catch me so easily it is insulting. <p>Gunreth Tunecrusher (Skald)<BR>
